# graphify exclusions for the KT pipeline
#
# GOAL: keep the corpus CODE-ONLY so graphify uses its deterministic,
# token-free AST path and never fires the LLM semantic extractor (Part B).
# Semantic extraction only runs for docs/papers/images — so by excluding
# all non-source files below, the graphify build stays near zero-token.

# Skill/tooling definitions — not registry-service source. Including them
# pollutes the graph with graphify/cartographer/kt nodes.
.claude/

# Pipeline-GENERATED documents. These are produced BY the KT pipeline.
# Graphing them is circular: it costs LLM tokens AND adds doc nodes that
# are not part of the actual service code. The later phases read these
# files directly, so they never need to be in the graph.
docs/
graphify-out/
TOKEN_REPORT.md
VALIDATION_REPORT.md

# Project markdown / help — consumed directly by acquire-codebase-knowledge
# (which searches for README/PRD/etc.), not needed in the code graph.
*.md

# Compiled output and bundled assets (also includes vendored JS/HTML that
# would otherwise be AST-extracted and clutter the graph).
target/

# Local tooling scripts that are not part of the service source.
kt-token-report.py
